msgstr "<primary>OpenVPN</primary><secondary>interfície de xarxa</secondary>"

msgid "With this configuration, starting OpenVPN creates the virtual network interface, usually under the <literal>tun0</literal> name. However, firewalls are often configured at the same time as the real network interfaces, which happens before OpenVPN starts. Good practice therefore recommends creating a persistent virtual network interface, and configuring OpenVPN to use this pre-existing interface. This further allows choosing the name for this interface. To this end, <command>openvpn --mktun --dev vpn --dev-type tun</command> creates a virtual network interface named <literal>vpn</literal> with type <literal>tun</literal>; this command can easily be integrated in the firewall configuration script, or in an <literal>up</literal> directive of the <filename>/etc/network/interfaces</filename> file, or a <emphasis role=\"package\">udev</emphasis> rule can be added to that end. The OpenVPN configuration file must also be updated accordingly, with the <literal>dev vpn</literal> and <literal>dev-type tun</literal> directives."
msgstr "Amb aquesta configuració, a l'engegar l'OpenVPN crea la interfície de xarxa virtual, normalment amb el nom <literal>tun0</literal>. No obstant això, els tallafocs es configuren sovint al mateix temps que les interfícies de xarxa reals, que ocorre abans que comenci l'OpenVPN. Per tant, una bona pràctica recomana crear una interfície de xarxa virtual persistent, i configurar l'OpenVPN per utilitzar aquesta interfície preexistent. Això també permet triar el nom d'aquesta interfície. A aquest efecte, <command>openvpn --mktun --dev vpn --dev-type tun</command> crea una interfície de xarxa virtual anomenada <literal>vpn</literal> de tipus <literal>tun</literal>; aquesta ordre es pot integrar fàcilment a l'script de configuració del tallafocs, o en una directiva <literal>up</literal> del fitxer <filename>/etc/network/interfaces</filename>, o una regla <emphasis role=\"package\">udev</emphasis> es pot crear amb aquesta fi. El fitxer de configuració d'OpenVPN també s'ha d'actualitzar en conseqüència amb les directives <literal>dev vpn</literal> i <literal>dev-type tun</literal>."

msgid "<primary>OpenVPN</primary><secondary>push route</secondary>"
msgstr "<primary>OpenVPN</primary><secondary>push route</secondary>"

msgid "Barring further action, VPN clients can only access the VPN server itself by way of the <literal>10.8.0.1</literal> address. Granting the clients access to the local network (192.168.0.0/24), requires adding a <literal>push route 192.168.0.0 255.255.255.0</literal> directive to the OpenVPN configuration so that VPN clients automatically get a network route telling them that this network is reachable by way of the VPN. Furthermore, machines on the local network also need to be informed that the route to the VPN goes through the VPN server (this automatically works when the VPN server is installed on the gateway). Alternatively, the VPN server can be configured to perform IP masquerading so that connections coming from VPN clients appear as if they are coming from the VPN server instead (see <xref linkend=\"sect.gateway\" />)."
msgstr "Sense fer res més, els clients VPN només poden accedir al servidor VPN a través de l'adreça <literal>10.8.0.1</literal>. La concessió als clients d'accés a la xarxa local (192.168.0.0/24), requereix l'addició d'una directiva <literal>push route 192.168.0.0 255.255.255.0</literal> a la configuració de l'OpenVPN perquè els clients VPN obtinguin automàticament una ruta de xarxa que els digui que aquesta xarxa és accessible a través de la VPN. A més, les màquines de la xarxa local també han de ser informades que la ruta cap a la VPN passa pel servidor VPN (això funciona automàticament quan el servidor VPN està instal·lat a la passarel·la d'entrada). Alternativament, el servidor VPN es pot configurar per realitzar emmascaraments IP de manera que les connexions procedents de clients VPN apareguin com si vinguessin del servidor VPN (vegeu <xref linkend=\"sect.gateway\" />)."

msgid "Configuring the OpenVPN Client"
msgstr "Configuració del cliente OpenVPN"

msgid "<primary>OpenVPN</primary><secondary>client</secondary>"
msgstr "<primary>OpenVPN</primary><secondary>client</secondary>"

msgid "Setting up an OpenVPN client also requires creating a configuration file in <filename>/etc/openvpn/</filename>. A standard configuration can be obtained by using <filename>/usr/share/doc/openvpn/examples/sample-config-files/client.conf</filename> as a starting point. The <literal>remote vpn.falcot.com 1194</literal> directive describes the address and port of the OpenVPN server; the <literal>ca</literal>, <literal>cert</literal> and <literal>key</literal> also need to be adapted to describe the locations of the key files."
msgstr "Configurar un client OpenVPN també requereix crear un fitxer de configuració a <filename>/etc/openvpn/</filename>. Es pot obtenir una configuració estàndard utilitzant <filename>/usr/share/doc/openvpn/examples/sample-config-files/client.conf</filename> com a punt d'inici. La directiva <literal>remote vpn.falcot.com 1194</literal> descriu l'adreça i el port del servidor OpenVPN; <literal>ca</literal>, <literal>cert</literal> i <literal>key</literal> també s'han d'adaptar per descriure les ubicacions dels fitxers de claus."

msgid "<primary>OpenVPN</primary><secondary><literal>AUTOSTART</literal></secondary>"
msgstr "<primary>OpenVPN</primary><secondary><literal>AUTOSTART</literal></secondary>"

msgid "<primary><filename>/etc</filename></primary><secondary>/etc/default/openvpn</secondary>"
msgstr "<primary><filename>/etc</filename></primary><secondary>/etc/default/openvpn</secondary>"

msgid "<primary>service</primary><secondary><filename>openvpn@.service</filename></secondary>"
msgstr "<primary>servei</primary><secondary><filename>openvpn@.service</filename></secondary>"

msgid "If the VPN should not be started automatically on boot, set the <literal>AUTOSTART</literal> directive to <literal>none</literal> in the <filename>/etc/default/openvpn</filename> file. Starting or stopping a given VPN connection is always possible with the commands <command>systemctl start openvpn@<replaceable>name</replaceable></command> and <command>systemctl stop openvpn@<replaceable>name</replaceable></command> (where the connection <replaceable>name</replaceable> matches the one defined in <filename>/etc/openvpn/<replaceable>name</replaceable>.conf</filename>)."
msgstr "Si la VPN no s'ha d'iniciar automàticament en arrencar, establiu la directiva <literal>AUTOSTART</literal> com a <literal>none</literal> al fitxer <filename>/etc/default/openvpn</filename>. Començar o aturar una connexió VPN donada sempre és possible amb les ordres <command>systemctl start openvpn@<replaceable>nom</replaceable></command> i <command>systemctl stop openvpn@<replaceable>nom</replaceable></command> (on la connexió<replaceable>nom</replaceable> coincideix amb la definida a <filename>/etc/openvpn/<replaceable>nom</replaceable>.conf</filename>)."

msgid "<primary>OpenVPN</primary><secondary><emphasis role=\"pkg\">network-manager-openvpn-gnome</emphasis></secondary>"
msgstr "<primary>OpenVPN</primary><secondary><emphasis role=\"pkg\">network-manager-openvpn-gnome</emphasis></secondary>"

msgid "The <emphasis role=\"pkg\">network-manager-openvpn-gnome</emphasis> package contains an extension to Network Manager (see <xref linkend=\"sect.roaming-network-config\" />) that allows managing OpenVPN virtual private networks. This allows every user to configure OpenVPN connections graphically and to control them from the network management icon."
msgstr "El paquet <emphasis role=\"pkg\">network-manager-openvpn-gnome</emphasis> conté una extensió del Network Manager (vegeu <xref linkend=\"sect.roaming-network-config\" />) que permet gestionar les xarxes privades virtuals d'OpenVPN. Això permet a tots els usuaris configurar les connexions OpenVPN gràficament i controlar-les des de la icona de gestió de xarxa."

msgid "<primary><emphasis role=\"pkg\">network-manager-openvpn-gnome</emphasis></primary>"
msgstr "<primary><emphasis role=\"pkg\">network-manager-openvpn-gnome</emphasis></primary>"

msgid "Virtual Private Network with SSH"
msgstr "Xarxa privada virtual amb SSH"

msgid "<primary>SSH</primary><secondary>VPN</secondary>"
msgstr "<primary>SSH</primary><secondary>VPN</secondary>"

msgid "<primary>PPP</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>PPP</primary>"

msgid "There are actually two ways of creating a virtual private network with SSH. The historic one involves establishing a PPP layer over the SSH link. This method is described in a HOWTO document: <ulink type=\"block\" url=\"https://www.tldp.org/HOWTO/ppp-ssh/\" />"
msgstr "En realitat hi ha dues maneres de crear una xarxa privada virtual amb SSH. La manera antiga consisteix en establir una capa PPP sobre l'enllaç SSH. Aquest mètode es descriu en un document HOWTO: <ulink type=\"block\" url=\"https://www.tldp.org/HOWTO/ppp-ssh/\" />"

msgid "<primary>SSH</primary><secondary><literal>PermitTunnel</literal></secondary>"
msgstr "<primary>SSH</primary><secondary><literal>PermitTunnel</literal></secondary>"

msgid "<primary><filename>/etc</filename></primary><secondary><filename>/etc/ssh/sshd_config</filename></secondary>"
msgstr "<primary><filename>/etc</filename></primary><secondary><filename>/etc/ssh/sshd_config</filename></secondary>"

msgid "The second method is more recent, and was introduced with OpenSSH 4.3; it is now possible for OpenSSH to create virtual network interfaces (<literal>tun*</literal>) on both sides of an SSH connection, and these virtual interfaces can be configured exactly as if they were physical interfaces. The tunneling system must first be enabled by setting <literal>PermitTunnel</literal> to “yes” in the SSH server configuration file (<filename>/etc/ssh/sshd_config</filename>). When establishing the SSH connection, the creation of a tunnel must be explicitly requested with the <literal>-w any:any</literal> option (<literal>any</literal> can be replaced with the desired <literal>tun</literal> device number). This requires the user to have administrator privilege on both sides, so as to be able to create the network device (in other words, the connection must be established as root)."
msgstr "El segon mètode és més recent, i es va introduir amb OpenSSH 4.3; ara és possible que OpenSSH creï interfícies de xarxa virtual (<literal>tun*</literal>) a ambdós costats d'una connexió SSH, i aquestes interfícies virtuals es poden configurar exactament com si fossin interfícies físiques. El sistema de tunelització s'ha d'activar primer establint <literal>PermitTunnel</literal> a «yes» al fitxer de configuració del servidor SSH (<filename>/etc/ssh/sshd_config</filename>). En establir la connexió SSH, la creació d'un túnel ha de ser explícitament sol·licitada amb l'opció <literal>-w any:any</literal> (<literal>any</literal> pot ser substituït amb el nombre de dispositiu <literal>tun</literal> desitjat). Això requereix que l'usuari tingui privilegis d'administrador en ambdós costats, per tal de poder crear el dispositiu de xarxa (en altres paraules, la connexió s'ha d'establir com a usuari arrel)."

msgid "Both methods for creating a virtual private network over SSH are quite straightforward. However, the VPN they provide is not the most efficient available; in particular, it does not handle high levels of traffic very well."
msgstr "Tots dos mètodes per crear una xarxa privada virtual a través de SSH són bastant senzills. No obstant això, la VPN que proporcionen no és la més eficient disponible; en particular, no gestiona massa bé els nivells alts de trànsit."

msgid "The explanation is that when a TCP/IP stack is encapsulated within a TCP/IP connection (for SSH), the TCP protocol is used twice, once for the SSH connection and once within the tunnel. This leads to problems, especially due to the way TCP adapts to network conditions by altering timeout delays. The following site describes the problem in more detail: <ulink type=\"block\" url=\"http://sites.inka.de/sites/bigred/devel/tcp-tcp.html\" />"
msgstr "L'explicació és que quan una pila TCP/IP es troba encapsulada dins d'una connexió TCP/IP (per a SSH), el protocol TCP s'utilitza dues vegades, una vegada per a la connexió SSH i una vegada dins del túnel. Això comporta problemes, especialment a causa de la forma en què TCP s'adapta a les condicions de la xarxa alterant els retards de temps d'espera. El següent lloc descriu el problema amb més detall: <ulink type=\"block\" url=\"http://sites.inka.de/sites/bigred/devel/tcp-tcp.html\" />"

msgid "VPNs over SSH should therefore be restricted to one-off tunnels with no performance constraints."
msgstr "Per tant, les VPN sobre SSH s'han de restringir a túnels únics sense restriccions de rendiment."

msgid "IPsec"
msgstr "IPsec"

msgid "<primary>IPsec</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>IPsec</primary>"

msgid "<primary>Internet Protocol Security</primary><see>IPsec</see>"
msgstr "<primary>Internet Protocol Security</primary><see>IPsec</see>"

msgid "<primary><command>libreswan</command></primary>"
msgstr "<primary><command>libreswan</command></primary>"

msgid "<primary><command>strongswan</command></primary>"
msgstr "<primary><command>strongswan</command></primary>"

msgid "IPsec, despite being the standard in IP VPNs, is rather more involved in its implementation. The IPsec engine itself is integrated in the Linux kernel; the required user-space parts, the control and configuration tools, are provided by the <emphasis role=\"pkg\">libreswan</emphasis> package or the <emphasis role=\"pkg\">strongswan</emphasis> package. Here we describe briefly the first of these options."
msgstr "IPsec, malgrat ser l'estàndard en les VPNs IP, està més implicat en la seva implementació. El motor IPsec està integrat al nucli de Linux; les parts necessàries de l'espai d'usuari, les eines de control i configuració són proporcionades pel paquet <emphasis role=\"pkg\">libreswan</emphasis> o el paquet <emphasis role=\"pkg\">strongswan</emphasis>. Aquí descriurem breument la primera d'aquestes opcions."

msgid "<primary><filename>/etc</filename></primary><secondary><filename>/etc/ipsec.conf</filename></secondary>"
msgstr "<primary><filename>/etc</filename></primary><secondary><filename>/etc/ipsec.conf</filename></secondary>"

msgid "<primary>IPsec</primary><secondary>tunnel</secondary>"
msgstr "<primary>IPsec</primary><secondary>túnel</secondary>"

msgid "First, we install the <emphasis role=\"pkg\">libreswan</emphasis> package. In concrete terms, each host's <filename>/etc/ipsec.conf</filename> contains the parameters for <emphasis>IPsec tunnels</emphasis> (or <emphasis>Security Associations</emphasis>, in the IPsec terminology) that the host is concerned with. There are many configuration examples in <filename>/usr/share/doc/libreswan/</filename>, but Libreswan's online documentation has more examples with explanations: <ulink type=\"block\" url=\"https://libreswan.org/wiki/\" />"
msgstr "Primer, instal·lem el paquet <emphasis role=\"pkg\">libreswan</emphasis>. En termes concrets, el <filename>/etc/ipsec.conf</filename> de cada equip conté els paràmetres per a <emphasis>túnels IPsec</emphasis> (o <emphasis>Security Associations</emphasis>, en la terminologia IPsec) de què el servidor s'ocupa. Hi ha molts exemples de configuració a <filename>/usr/share/doc/libreswan/</filename>, però la documentació en línia de Libreswan té més exemples amb explicacions: <ulink type=\"block\" url=\"https://libreswan.org/wiki/\" />"

msgid "<primary>service</primary><secondary><filename>ipsec.service</filename></secondary>"
msgstr "<primary>servei</primary><secondary><filename>ipsec.service</filename></secondary>"

msgid "The IPsec service can be controlled with <command>systemctl</command>; for example, <command>systemctl start ipsec</command> will start the IPsec service."
msgstr "El servei IPsec es pot controlar amb <command>systemctl</command>; per exemple, <command>systemctl start ipsec</command> iniciarà el servei IPsec."

msgid "<primary>IKE</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>IKE</primary>"

msgid "<primary>IPsec Key Exchange</primary><see>IKE</see>"
msgstr "<primary>IPsec Key Exchange</primary><see>IKE</see>"

msgid "<primary>IPsec</primary><secondary>IPsec Key Exchange</secondary><seealso>IKE</seealso>"
msgstr "<primary>IPsec</primary><secondary>IPsec Key Exchange</secondary><seealso>IKE</seealso>"

msgid "<primary><command>setkey</command></primary>"
msgstr "<primary><command>setkey</command></primary>"

msgid "In spite of its status as the reference, the complexity of setting up IPsec restricts its usage in practice. OpenVPN-based solutions will generally be preferred when the required tunnels are neither too many nor too dynamic."
msgstr "Malgrat el seu estatus com a referència, la complexitat de la configuració d'IPsec restringeix el seu ús en la pràctica. Les solucions basades en OpenVPN es preferiran generalment quan els túnels requerits no siguin masses ni massa dinàmics."

msgid "<emphasis>CAUTION</emphasis> IPsec and NAT"
msgstr "<emphasis>COMPTE</emphasis> IPsec i NAT"

msgid "<primary>NAT</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>NAT</primary>"

msgid "<primary>NAT-T</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>NAT-T</primary>"

msgid "<primary>NAT Traversal</primary><seealso>NAT-T</seealso>"
msgstr "<primary>NAT Traversal</primary><seealso>NAT-T</seealso>"

msgid "NATing firewalls and IPsec do not work well together: since IPsec signs the packets, any change on these packets that the firewall might perform will void the signature, and the packets will be rejected at their destination. Various IPsec implementations now include the <emphasis>NAT-T</emphasis> technique (for <emphasis>NAT Traversal</emphasis>), which basically encapsulates the IPsec packet within a standard UDP packet."
msgstr "Els tallafocs que fan NAT i IPsec no funcionen bé junts: com que IPsec signa els paquets, qualsevol canvi en aquests paquets que el tallafoc pugui realitzar anul·larà la signatura, i els paquets seran rebutjats al destí. Diverses implementacions IPsec ara inclouen la tècnica <emphasis>NAT-T</emphasis> (<emphasis>NAT Traversal</emphasis>), que bàsicament encapsula el paquet IPsec dins d'un paquet UDP estàndard."

msgid "<emphasis>SECURITY</emphasis> IPsec and firewalls"
msgstr "<emphasis>SEGURETAT</emphasis> IPsec i tallafocs"

msgid "<primary>ESP, protocol</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>ESP, protocol</primary>"

msgid "<primary>AH, protocol</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>AH, protocol</primary>"

msgid "<primary>protocol</primary><secondary>AH</secondary>"
msgstr "<primary>protocol</primary><secondary>AH</secondary>"

msgid "<primary>protocol</primary><secondary>ESP</secondary>"
msgstr "<primary>protocol</primary><secondary>ESP</secondary>"

msgid "The standard mode of operation of IPsec involves data exchanges on UDP port 500 for key exchanges (also on UDP port 4500 in the case that NAT-T is in use). Moreover, IPsec packets use two dedicated IP protocols that the firewall must let through; reception of these packets is based on their protocol numbers, 50 (ESP) and 51 (AH)."
msgstr "El mode estàndard d'operació d'IPsec implica intercanvis de dades al port UDP 500 per a intercanvis de claus (també al port UDP 4500 en el cas que el NAT-T estigui en ús). A més, els paquets IPsec utilitzen dos protocols IP dedicats que el tallafocs ha de deixar passar; la recepció d'aquests paquets es basa en els seus números de protocol, 50 (ESP) i 51 (AH)."

msgid "PPTP"
msgstr "PPTP"

msgid "<primary>PPTP</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>PPTP</primary>"

msgid "<primary>GRE, protocol</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>GRE, protocol</primary>"

msgid "<primary>protocol</primary><secondary>GRE</secondary>"
msgstr "<primary>protocol</primary><secondary>GRE</secondary>"

msgid "PPTP (for <emphasis>Point-to-Point Tunneling Protocol</emphasis>) uses two communication channels, one for control data and one for payload data; the latter uses the GRE protocol (<emphasis>Generic Routing Encapsulation</emphasis>). A standard PPP link is then set up over the data exchange channel."
msgstr "PPTP (de «<emphasis>Point-to-Point Tunneling Protocol</emphasis>» o “Protocol de túnel punt a punt”) utilitza dos canals de comunicació, un per a les dades de control i un altre per a les dades; aquest últim utilitza el protocol GRE («<emphasis>Generic Routing Encapsulation</emphasis>» o “Encapsulació d'encaminament genèric”). A continuació es crea un enllaç PPP estàndard sobre el canal d'intercanvi de dades."

msgid "Configuring the Client"
msgstr "Configuració del client"

msgid "<primary>PPTP</primary><secondary>Client</secondary>"
msgstr "<primary>PPTP</primary><secondary>Client</secondary>"

msgid "<primary><emphasis role=\"pkg\">pptp-linux</emphasis></primary>"
msgstr "<primary><emphasis role=\"pkg\">pptp-linux</emphasis></primary>"

msgid "The <emphasis role=\"pkg\">pptp-linux</emphasis> package contains an easily-configured PPTP client for Linux. The following instructions take their inspiration from the official documentation: <ulink type=\"block\" url=\"http://pptpclient.sourceforge.net/howto-debian.phtml\" />"
msgstr "El paquet <emphasis role=\"pkg\">pptp-linux</emphasis> conté un client PPTP fàcilment configurable per a Linux. Les següents instruccions s'inspiren en la documentació oficial: <ulink type=\"block\" url=\"http://pptpclient.sourceforge.net/howto-debian.phtml\" />"

msgid "<primary><filename>/etc</filename></primary><secondary><filename>/etc/ppp/</filename></secondary>"
msgstr "<primary><filename>/etc</filename></primary><secondary><filename>/etc/ppp/</filename></secondary>"

msgid "The Falcot administrators created several files: <filename>/etc/ppp/options.pptp</filename>, <filename>/etc/ppp/peers/falcot</filename>, <filename>/etc/ppp/ip-up.d/falcot</filename>, and <filename>/etc/ppp/ip-down.d/falcot</filename>."
msgstr "Els administradors de Falcot van crear diversos fitxers: <filename>/etc/ppp/options.pptp</filename>, <filename>/etc/ppp/peers/falcot</filename>, <filename>/etc/ppp/ip-up.d/falcot</filename>, i <filename>/etc/ppp/ip-down.d/falcot</filename>."

msgid "The <filename>/etc/ppp/options.pptp</filename> file"
msgstr "El fitxer <filename>/etc/ppp/options.pptp</filename>"

msgid ""
"\n"
"# PPP options used for a PPTP connection\n"
"lock\n"
"noauth\n"
"nobsdcomp\n"
"nodeflate"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"# opcions PPP usades en una connexió PPTP\n"
"lock\n"
"noauth\n"
"nobsdcomp\n"
"nodeflate"

msgid "The <filename>/etc/ppp/peers/falcot</filename> file"
msgstr "El fitxer <filename>/etc/ppp/peers/falcot</filename>"

msgid ""
"\n"
"# vpn.falcot.com is the PPTP server\n"
"pty \"pptp vpn.falcot.com --nolaunchpppd\"\n"
"# the connection will identify as the \"vpn\" user\n"
"user vpn\n"
"remotename pptp\n"
"# encryption is needed\n"
"require-mppe-128\n"
"file /etc/ppp/options.pptp\n"
"ipparam falcot"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"# vpn.falcot.com és el servidor PPTP\n"
"pty \"pptp vpn.falcot.com --nolaunchpppd\"\n"
"# la connexió s'identificarà usant l'usuari \"vpn\"\n"
"user vpn\n"
"remotename pptp\n"
"# es necessita xifratge\n"
"require-mppe-128\n"
"file /etc/ppp/options.pptp\n"
"ipparam falcot"

msgid "The <filename>/etc/ppp/ip-up.d/falcot</filename> file"
msgstr "El fitxer <filename>/etc/ppp/ip-up.d/falcot</filename>"

msgid ""
"\n"
"# Create the route to the Falcot network\n"
"if [ \"$6\" = \"falcot\" ]; then\n"
"  # 192.168.0.0/24 is the (remote) Falcot network\n"
"  ip route add 192.168.0.0/24 dev $1\n"
"fi"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"# Crea la ruta cap a la xarxa de Falcot\n"
"if [ \"$6\" = \"falcot\" ]; then\n"
"  # 192.168.0.0/24 és la xarxa (remota) de Falcot\n"
"  ip route add 192.168.0.0/24 dev $1\n"
"fi"

msgid "The <filename>/etc/ppp/ip-down.d/falcot</filename> file"
msgstr "El fitxer <filename>/etc/ppp/ip-down.d/falcot</filename>"

msgid ""
"\n"
"# Delete the route to the Falcot network\n"
"if [ \"$6\" = \"falcot\" ]; then\n"
"  # 192.168.0.0/24 is the (remote) Falcot network\n"
"  ip route del 192.168.0.0/24 dev $1\n"
"fi"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"# Elimina la ruta cap a la xarxa de Falcol\n"
"if [ \"$6\" = \"falcot\" ]; then\n"
"  # 192.168.0.0/24 és la xarxa (remota) de Falcot\n"
"  ip route del 192.168.0.0/24 dev $1\n"
"fi"

msgid "<emphasis>SECURITY</emphasis> MPPE"
msgstr "<emphasis>SEGURETAT</emphasis> MPPE"

msgid "<primary>MPPE</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>MPPE</primary>"

msgid "<primary>Microsoft</primary><secondary>Point-to-Point Encryption</secondary><see>MPPE</see>"
msgstr "<primary>Microsoft</primary><secondary>Point-to-Point Encryption</secondary><see>MPPE</see>"

msgid "Securing PPTP involves using the MPPE feature (<emphasis>Microsoft Point-to-Point Encryption</emphasis>), which is available in official Debian kernels as a module."
msgstr "Per fer segur PPTP cal utilitzar la característica MPPE («<emphasis>Microsoft Point-to-Point Encryption</emphasis>» o “Xifratge punt a punt de Microsoft”), que està disponible en els nuclis oficials de Debian com a mòdul."

msgid "Configuring the Server"
msgstr "Configuració del servidor"

msgid "<primary><command>pptpd</command></primary>"
msgstr "<primary><command>pptpd</command></primary>"

msgid "<emphasis>CAUTION</emphasis> PPTP and firewalls"
msgstr "<emphasis>COMPTE</emphasis> PPTP i tallafocs"

msgid "Intermediate firewalls need to be configured to let through IP packets using protocol 47 (GRE). Moreover, the PPTP server's port 1723 needs to be open so that the communication channel can happen."
msgstr "Els tallafocs intermedis s'han de configurar per permetre el pas de paquets IP que usin el protocol 47 (GRE). A més, el port 1723 del servidor PPTP ha d'estar obert perquè el canal de comunicació pugui establir-se."

msgid "<primary><filename>/etc</filename></primary><secondary><filename>/etc/pptpd.conf</filename></secondary>"
msgstr "<primary><filename>/etc</filename></primary><secondary><filename>/etc/pptpd.conf</filename></secondary>"

msgid "<command>pptpd</command> is the PPTP server for Linux. Its main configuration file, <filename>/etc/pptpd.conf</filename>, requires very few changes: <emphasis>localip</emphasis> (local IP address) and <emphasis>remoteip</emphasis> (remote IP address). In the example below, the PPTP server always uses the <literal>192.168.0.199</literal> address, and PPTP clients receive IP addresses from <literal>192.168.0.200</literal> to <literal>192.168.0.250</literal>."
msgstr "<command>pptpd</command> és el servidor PPTP per a Linux. El seu fitxer de configuració principal, <filename>/etc/pptpd.conf</filename>, requereix molt pocs canvis: <emphasis>localip</emphasis> (adreça IP local) i <emphasis>remoteip</emphasis> (adreça IP remota). En l'exemple següent, el servidor PPTP sempre utilitza l'adreça <literal>192.168.0.199</literal>, i els clients PPTP reben adreces IP de <literal>192.168.0.200</literal> a <literal>192.168.0.250</literal>."

msgid "The <filename>/etc/pptpd.conf</filename> file"
msgstr "El fitxer <filename>/etc/pptpd.conf</filename>"

msgid ""
"\n"
"[..]\n"
"# TAG: localip\n"
"# TAG: remoteip\n"
"#       Specifies the local and remote IP address ranges.\n"
"#\n"
"#       These options are ignored if delegate option is set.\n"
"#\n"
"#       Any addresses work as long as the local machine takes care of the\n"
"#       routing.  But if you want to use MS-Windows networking, you should\n"
"#       use IP addresses out of the LAN address space and use the proxyarp\n"
"#       option in the pppd options file, or run bcrelay.\n"
"#\n"
"#       You can specify single IP addresses seperated by commas or you can\n"
"#       specify ranges, or both. For example:\n"
"#\n"
"#               192.168.0.234,192.168.0.245-249,192.168.0.254\n"
"#\n"
"#       IMPORTANT RESTRICTIONS:\n"
"#\n"
"#       1. No spaces are permitted between commas or within addresses.\n"
"#\n"
"#       2. If you give more IP addresses than the value of connections,\n"
"#          it will start at the beginning of the list and go until it\n"
"#          gets connections IPs.  Others will be ignored.\n"
"#\n"
"#       3. No shortcuts in ranges! ie. 234-8 does not mean 234 to 238,\n"
"#          you must type 234-238 if you mean this.\n"
"#\n"
"#       4. If you give a single localIP, that's ok - all local IPs will\n"
"#          be set to the given one. You MUST still give at least one remote\n"
"#          IP for each simultaneous client.\n"
"#\n"
"# (Recommended)\n"
"#localip 192.168.0.1\n"
"#remoteip 192.168.0.234-238,192.168.0.245\n"
"# or\n"
"#localip 192.168.0.234-238,192.168.0.245\n"
"#remoteip 192.168.1.234-238,192.168.1.245\n"
"localip 192.168.0.199\n"
"remoteip 192.168.0.200-250"
msgstr "\n[..]\n# TAG: localip\n# TAG: remoteip\n#       Specifies the local and remote IP address ranges.\n#\n#       These options are ignored if delegate option is set.\n#\n#       Any addresses work as long as the local machine takes care of the\n#       routing.  But if you want to use MS-Windows networking, you should\n#       use IP addresses out of the LAN address space and use the proxyarp\n#       option in the pppd options file, or run bcrelay.\n#\n#       You can specify single IP addresses seperated by commas or you can\n#       specify ranges, or both. For example:\n#\n#               192.168.0.234,192.168.0.245-249,192.168.0.254\n#\n#       IMPORTANT RESTRICTIONS:\n#\n#       1. No spaces are permitted between commas or within addresses.\n#\n#       2. If you give more IP addresses than the value of connections,\n#          it will start at the beginning of the list and go until it\n#          gets connections IPs.  Others will be ignored.\n#\n#       3. No shortcuts in ranges! ie. 234-8 does not mean 234 to 238,\n#          you must type 234-238 if you mean this.\n#\n#       4. If you give a single localIP, that's ok - all local IPs will\n#          be set to the given one. You MUST still give at least one remote\n#          IP for each simultaneous client.\n#\n# (Recommended)\n#localip 192.168.0.1\n#remoteip 192.168.0.234-238,192.168.0.245\n# or\n#localip 192.168.0.234-238,192.168.0.245\n#remoteip 192.168.1.234-238,192.168.1.245\nlocalip 192.168.0.199\nremoteip 192.168.0.200-250"

msgid "<primary><filename>/etc</filename></primary><secondary><filename>/etc/ppp/pptpd-options</filename></secondary>"
msgstr "<primary><filename>/etc</filename></primary><secondary><filename>/etc/ppp/pptpd-options</filename></secondary>"

msgid "The PPP configuration used by the PPTP server also requires a few changes in <filename>/etc/ppp/pptpd-options</filename>. The important parameters are the server name (<literal>pptp</literal>), the domain name (<literal>falcot.com</literal>), and the IP addresses for DNS and WINS servers."
msgstr "La configuració PPP utilitzada pel servidor PPTP també requereix alguns canvis a <filename>/etc/ppp/pptpd-options</filename>. Els paràmetres importants són el nom del servidor (<literal>pptp</literal>), el nom del domini (<literal>falcot.com</literal>), i les adreces IP dels servidors de DNS i WINS."

msgid "The <filename>/etc/ppp/pptpd-options</filename> file"
msgstr "El fitxer <filename>/etc/ppp/pptpd-options</filename>"

msgid ""
"\n"
"# Enable connection debugging facilities.\n"
"# (see your syslog configuration for where pppd sends to)\n"
"#debug\n"
"\n"
"# Name of the local system for authentication purposes\n"
"# (must match the second field in /etc/ppp/chap-secrets entries)\n"
"name pptpd\n"
"\n"
"# Optional: domain name to use for authentication\n"
"## change the domainname to your local domain\n"
"domain falcot.com\n"
"\n"
"# Authentication\n"
"## these are reasonable defaults for WinXXXX clients\n"
"## for the security related settings\n"
"auth\n"
"refuse-pap\n"
"refuse-chap\n"
"refuse-mschap\n"
"# Require the peer to authenticate itself using MS-CHAPv2 [Microsoft\n"
"# Challenge Handshake Authentication Protocol, Version 2] authentication.\n"
"require-mschap-v2\n"
"# Require MPPE 128-bit encryption\n"
"# (note that MPPE requires the use of MSCHAP-V2 during authentication)\n"
"require-mppe-128\n"
"\n"
"# Network and Routing\n"
"## Fill in your addresses\n"
"ms-dns 192.168.0.1\n"
"ms-wins 192.168.0.1\n"
"\n"
"## Fill in your netmask\n"
"netmask 255.255.255.0\n"
"\n"
"## some defaults\n"
"nodefaultroute\n"
"proxyarp\n"
"lock"
msgstr "\n# Enable connection debugging facilities.\n# (see your syslog configuration for where pppd sends to)\n#debug\n\n# Name of the local system for authentication purposes\n# (must match the second field in /etc/ppp/chap-secrets entries)\nname pptpd\n\n# Optional: domain name to use for authentication\n## change the domainname to your local domain\ndomain falcot.com\n\n# Authentication\n## these are reasonable defaults for WinXXXX clients\n## for the security related settings\nauth\nrefuse-pap\nrefuse-chap\nrefuse-mschap\n# Require the peer to authenticate itself using MS-CHAPv2 [Microsoft\n# Challenge Handshake Authentication Protocol, Version 2] authentication.\nrequire-mschap-v2\n# Require MPPE 128-bit encryption\n# (note that MPPE requires the use of MSCHAP-V2 during authentication)\nrequire-mppe-128\n\n# Network and Routing\n## Fill in your addresses\nms-dns 192.168.0.1\nms-wins 192.168.0.1\n\n## Fill in your netmask\nnetmask 255.255.255.0\n\n## some defaults\nnodefaultroute\nproxyarp\nlock"

msgid "<primary><filename>/etc</filename></primary><secondary><filename>/etc/ppp/chap-secrets</filename></secondary>"
msgstr "<primary><filename>/etc</filename></primary><secondary><filename>/etc/ppp/chap-secrets</filename></secondary>"

msgid "The last step involves registering the <literal>vpn</literal> user (and the associated password) in the <filename>/etc/ppp/chap-secrets</filename> file. Contrary to other instances where an asterisk (<literal>*</literal>) would work, the server name must be filled explicitly here. Furthermore, Windows PPTP clients identify themselves under the <literal><replaceable>DOMAIN</replaceable>\\\\<replaceable>USER</replaceable></literal> form, instead of only providing a user name. This explains why the file also mentions the <literal>FALCOT\\\\vpn</literal> user. It is also possible to specify individual IP addresses for users; an asterisk in this field specifies that dynamic addressing should be used."
msgstr "L'últim pas consisteix a registrar l'usuari <literal>vpn</literal> (i la contrasenya associada) al fitxer <filename>/etc/ppp/chap-secrets</filename>. Contràriament a altres instàncies on funcionaria un asterisc (<literal>*</literal>), el nom del servidor s'ha d'explicitar aquí. A més, els clients PPTP de Windows s'identifiquen amb la forma <literal><replaceable>DOMINI</replaceable>\\\\<replaceable>USER</replaceable></literal>, en lloc de només proporcionar un nom d'usuari. Això explica per què el fitxer també esmenta l'usuari <literal>FALCOT\\\\vpn</literal>. També és possible especificar adreces IP individuals per als usuaris; un asterisc en aquest camp especifica que s'ha d'utilitzar l'adreçament dinàmic."

msgid "The <filename>/etc/ppp/chap-secrets</filename> file"
msgstr "El fitxer <filename>/etc/ppp/chap-secrets</filename>"

msgid ""
"\n"
"# Secrets for authentication using CHAP\n"
"# client        server  secret      IP addresses\n"
"vpn             pptp    f@Lc3au     *\n"
"FALCOT\\\\vpn     pptp    f@Lc3au     *"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"# Secrets per a l'autenticació usant CHAP\n"
"# client       servidor secret     adreça IP\n"
"vpn             pptp     f@Lc3au     *\n"
"FALCOT\\\\vpn     pptp     f@Lc3au     *"

msgid "<emphasis>SECURITY</emphasis> PPTP vulnerabilities"
msgstr "<emphasis>SEGURETAT</emphasis> Vulnerabilitats de PPTP"

msgid "<primary>PPTP</primary><secondary>vulnerabilities</secondary>"
msgstr "<primary>PPTP</primary><secondary>vulnerabilitats</secondary>"

msgid "Microsoft's first PPTP implementation drew severe criticism because it had many security vulnerabilities; most have since then been fixed in more recent versions. The configuration documented in this section uses the latest version of the protocol. Be aware though that removing some options (such as <literal>require-mppe-128</literal> and <literal>require-mschap-v2</literal>) would make the service vulnerable again."
msgstr "La primera implementació del PPTP per part de Microsoft va ser molt criticada perquè tenia moltes vulnerabilitats de seguretat; la majoria s'han solventat en versions més recents. La configuració documentada en aquesta secció utilitza l'última versió del protocol. Tingueu en compte que l'eliminació d'algunes opcions (com ara <literal>require-mppe-128</literal> i <literal>require-mschap-v2</literal>) faria el servei vulnerable altre cop."

msgid "Quality of Service"
msgstr "Qualitat del servei"

msgid "Principle and Mechanism"
msgstr "Principis i mecanisme"

msgid "<primary>network</primary><secondary>QoS</secondary>"
msgstr "<primary>xarxa</primary><secondary>QoS</secondary>"

msgid "<primary>QoS</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>QoS</primary>"

msgid "<primary>Quality of Service</primary><see>QoS</see>"
msgstr "<primary>Qualitat del servei</primary><see>QoS</see>"

msgid "<primary>quality</primary><secondary>of service</secondary><see>QoS</see>"
msgstr "<primary>qualitat</primary><secondary>del servei</secondary><see>QoS</see>"

msgid "<primary>service</primary><secondary>quality</secondary><see>QoS</see>"
msgstr "<primary>servei</primary><secondary>qualitat</secondary><see>QoS</see>"

msgid "<emphasis>Quality of Service</emphasis> (or <emphasis>QoS</emphasis> for short) refers to a set of techniques that guarantee or improve the quality of the service provided to applications. The most popular such technique involves classifying the network traffic into categories, and differentiating the handling of traffic according to which category it belongs to. The main application of this differentiated services concept is <emphasis>traffic shaping</emphasis>, which limits the data transmission rates for connections related to some services and/or hosts so as not to saturate the available bandwidth and starve important other services. Traffic shaping is a particularly good fit for TCP traffic, since this protocol automatically adapts to available bandwidth."
msgstr "<emphasis>Qualitat del Servei</emphasis> (o <emphasis>QoS</emphasis> per l'acrònim en anglès) es refereix a un conjunt de tècniques que garanteixen o milloren la qualitat del servei proporcionat a les aplicacions. La tècnica més popular consisteix a classificar el trànsit de xarxa en categories, i diferenciar el tractament del trànsit segons la categoria a la qual pertany. L'aplicació principal d'aquest concepte de serveis diferenciats és el «<emphasis>traffic shaping</emphasis>» o “modelatge del trànsit”, que limita les taxes de transmissió de dades per a connexions relacionades amb alguns serveis i/o servidors per no saturar l'amplada de banda disponible i fer que altres serveis es degradin. El «traffic shaping» és una tècnica especialment bona per al trànsit TCP, ja que aquest protocol s'adapta automàticament a l'amplada de banda disponible."

msgid "<emphasis>CULTURE</emphasis> Net neutrality and QoS"
msgstr "<emphasis>CULTURA</emphasis> Neutralitat de la xarxa i qualitat del servei"

msgid "<primary>network</primary><secondary>neutrality</secondary>"
msgstr "<primary>xarxa</primary><secondary>neutralitat</secondary>"

msgid "Network neutrality is achieved when Internet service providers treat all Internet communications equally, that is, without any access limitation based on content, user, website, destination address, etc."
msgstr "La neutralitat de la xarxa s'aconsegueix quan els proveïdors de serveis d'Internet tracten totes les comunicacions per Internet per igual, és a dir, sense cap limitació d'accés basat en el contingut, l'usuari, el lloc web, l'adreça de destinació, etc."

msgid "Quality of service can be implemented in a net neutral Internet, but only if Internet service providers can't charge a special fee for a higher-quality service."
msgstr "La qualitat del servei es pot implementar en una Internet amb neutralitat de xarxa, però només si els proveïdors de serveis d'Internet no poden cobrar una taxa especial per un servei d'alta qualitat."

msgid "It is also possible to alter the priorities on traffic, which allows prioritizing packets related to interactive services (such as <command>ssh</command> and <command>telnet</command>) or to services that only deal with small blocks of data."
msgstr "També és possible alterar les prioritats del trànsit, que permet prioritzar paquets relacionats amb serveis interactius (com ara <command>ssh</command> i <command>telnet</command>) o amb serveis que només tracten amb petits blocs de dades."

msgid "The Debian kernels include the features required for QoS along with their associated modules. These modules are many, and each of them provides a different service, most notably by way of special schedulers for the queues of IP packets; the wide range of available scheduler behaviors spans the whole range of possible requirements."
msgstr "Els nuclis de Debian inclouen les característiques necessàries per a QoS juntament amb els seus mòduls associats. Aquests mòduls són molts, i cadascun d'ells proporciona un servei diferent, sobretot a través de planificadors especials per a les cues de paquets IP; l'àmplia gamma de comportaments de planificadors disponibles abasta tot el rang de possibles requisits."

msgid "<emphasis>CULTURE</emphasis> LARTC — <emphasis>Linux Advanced Routing &amp; Traffic Control</emphasis>"
msgstr "<emphasis>CULTURA</emphasis> LARTC — «<emphasis>Linux Advanced Routing &amp; Traffic Control</emphasis>» o Encaminament avançat i control de trànsit de Linux"

msgid "<primary>network</primary><secondary>advanced routing</secondary><seealso>routing</seealso>"
msgstr "<primary>xarxa</primary><secondary>encaminament avançat</secondary><seealso>encaminament</seealso>"

msgid "<primary>routing</primary><secondary>advanced</secondary>"
msgstr "<primary>encaminament</primary><secondary>avançat</secondary>"

msgid "<primary>traffic</primary><secondary>control</secondary>"
msgstr "<primary>trànsit</primary><secondary>control</secondary>"

msgid "<primary>control of traffic</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>control de trànsit</primary>"

msgid "The <emphasis>Linux Advanced Routing &amp; Traffic Control</emphasis> HOWTO is the reference document covering everything there is to know about network quality of service. <ulink type=\"block\" url=\"https://www.lartc.org/howto/\" />"
msgstr "El «HOWTO» de «<emphasis>Linux Advanced Routing &amp; Traffic Control</emphasis>» és el document de referència que cobreix tot el que hi ha per saber sobre la qualitat del servei de la xarxa. <ulink type=\"block\" url=\"https://www.lartc.org/howto/\" />"

msgid "Configuring and Implementing"
msgstr "Configuració i implementació"

msgid "<primary><emphasis>iproute</emphasis></primary>"
msgstr "<primary><emphasis>iproute</emphasis></primary>"

msgid "<primary><command>tc</command></primary>"
msgstr "<primary><command>tc</command></primary>"

msgid "QoS parameters are set through the <command>tc</command> command (provided by the <emphasis role=\"pkg\">iproute</emphasis> package). Since its interface is quite complex, using higher-level tools is recommended."
msgstr "Els paràmetres de QoS s'estableixen a través de l'ordre <command>tc</command> (proveït pel paquet <emphasis role=\"pkg\">iproute</emphasis>). Com que la seva interfície és bastant complexa, es recomana utilitzar eines de nivell superior."

msgid "Reducing Latencies: <command>wondershaper</command>"
msgstr "Reducció de latències: <command>wondershaper</command>"

msgid "<primary><command>wondershaper</command></primary>"
msgstr "<primary><command>wondershaper</command></primary>"

msgid "<primary>limitation of traffic</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>limitació del trànsit</primary>"

msgid "<primary>traffic</primary><secondary>limitation</secondary>"
msgstr "<primary>trànsit</primary><secondary>limitació</secondary>"

msgid "The main purpose of <command>wondershaper</command> (in the similarly-named package) is to minimize latencies independent of network load. This is achieved by limiting total traffic to a value that falls just short of the link saturation value."
msgstr "El propòsit principal de <command>wondershaper</command> (al paquet del mateix nom) és minimitzar les latències independentment de la càrrega de la xarxa. Això s'aconsegueix limitant el trànsit total a un valor que quedi per sota del valor de saturació de l'enllaç."

msgid "Once a network interface is configured, setting up this traffic limitation is achieved by running <command>wondershaper <replaceable>interface</replaceable> <replaceable>download_rate</replaceable> <replaceable>upload_rate</replaceable></command>. The interface can be <literal>enp1s0</literal>, <literal>eth0</literal> or <literal>ppp0</literal> for example, and both rates are expressed in kilobits per second. The <command>wondershaper remove <replaceable>interface</replaceable></command> command disables traffic control on the specified interface."
msgstr "Un cop que s'ha configurat una interfície de xarxa, la limitació del trànsit s'aconsegueix executant <command>wondershaper <replaceable>interfície</replaceable> <replaceable></replaceable>taxa_de_baixada<replaceable>taxa_de_pujada</replaceable></command>. La interfície pot ser <literal>enp1s0</literal>, <literal>eth0</literal> o <literal>ppp0</literal>, per exemple, i ambdues taxes s'expressen en kilobits per segon. El <command>wondershaper remove <replaceable>interfície</replaceable></command> inhabilita el control de trànsit a la interfície especificada."

msgid "<primary><filename>/etc</filename></primary><secondary><filename>/etc/network/interfaces</filename></secondary>"
msgstr "<primary><filename>/etc</filename></primary><secondary><filename>/etc/network/interfaces</filename></secondary>"

msgid "For an Ethernet connection, historically this script would be called right after the interface is configured. This is done by adding <literal>up</literal> and <literal>down</literal> directives to the <filename>/etc/network/interfaces</filename> file allowing declared commands to be run, respectively, after the interface is configured and before it is deconfigured. Or in the PPP case, creating a script that calls <command>wondershaper</command> in <filename>/etc/ppp/ip-up.d/</filename> will enable traffic control as soon as the connection is up. Below is an example using this first method:"
msgstr "Per a una connexió Ethernet, històricament aquest script s'havia executat just després que la interfície estés configurada. Això es fa afegint directives <literal>up</literal> i <literal>down</literal> al fitxer <filename>/etc/network/interfaces</filename> que permet executar ordres declarades, respectivament, després que la interfície estigui configurada i abans que es desconfiguri. O en el cas del PPP, creant un script que cridi <command>wondershaper</command> a <filename>/etc/ppp/ip-up.d/</filename> activarà el control del trànsit així que la connexió s'estableixi. Tot seguit hi ha un exemple usant el primer mètode:"

msgid "Changes in the <filename>/etc/network/interfaces</filename> file"
msgstr "Canvis al fitxer <filename>/etc/network/interfaces</filename>"

msgid ""
"\n"
"iface eth0 inet dhcp\n"
"    up /sbin/wondershaper eth0 500 100\n"
"    down /sbin/wondershaper remove eth0"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"iface eth0 inet dhcp\n"
"    up /sbin/wondershaper eth0 500 100\n"
"    down /sbin/wondershaper remove eth0"

msgid "<emphasis>GOING FURTHER</emphasis> Optimal configuration"
msgstr "<emphasis>ANANT MÉS ENLLÀ</emphasis> Configuració òptima"

msgid "The <filename>/usr/share/doc/wondershaper/README.Debian.gz</filename> file describes, in some detail, the configuration method recommended by the package maintainer. In particular, it advises measuring the download and upload speeds so as to best evaluate real limits."
msgstr "El fitxer <filename>/usr/share/doc/wondershaper/README.Debian.gz</filename> descriu, en alguns detalls, el mètode de configuració recomanat pel mantenidor del paquet. En particular, aconsella mesurar les velocitats de pujada i baixada per tal d'avaluar millor els límits reals."

msgid "Standard Configuration"
msgstr "Configuració estàndar"

msgid "<primary>DSCP</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>DSCP</primary>"

msgid "<primary>Differentiated Services Code Point</primary><see>DSCP</see>"
msgstr "<primary>Differentiated Services Code Point</primary><see>DSCP</see>"

msgid "Barring a specific QoS configuration, the Linux kernel uses the <literal>pfifo_fast</literal> queue scheduler, which provides a few interesting features by itself. The priority of each processed IP packet is based on the DSCP field (<emphasis>Differentiated Services Code Point</emphasis>) of this packet; modifying this 6-bit field is enough to take advantage of the scheduling features. Refer to <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Differentiated_services#Class_Selector\" /> for more information."
msgstr "A manca d'una configuració específica de QoS, el nucli de Linux utilitza el planificador de cua <literal>pfifo_fast</literal> que proporciona algunes característiques interessants per si mateix. La prioritat de cada paquet IP processat es basa en el camp DSCP («<emphasis>Differentiated Services Code Point</emphasis>» o “punt de codi de serveis diferenciats”) del propi paquet; modificar aquest camp de 6 bits és suficient per aprofitar les característiques de planificació. Consulteu <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Differentiated_services#Class_Selector\" /> per a més informació."

msgid "<primary>IP</primary><secondary>netfilter</secondary>"
msgstr "<primary>IP</primary><secondary>netfilter</secondary>"

msgid "The DSCP field can be set by applications that generate IP packets, or modified on the fly by <emphasis>netfilter</emphasis>. The following rules are sufficient to increase responsiveness for a server's SSH service, note that the DSCP field must be set in hexadecimal:"
msgstr "El camp DSCP pot ser establert per aplicacions que generen paquets IP, o modificat sobre la marxa per <emphasis>netfilter</emphasis>. Les següents regles són suficients per augmentar la capacitat de resposta per al servei d'SSH d'un servidor, però tingueu en compte que el camp DSCP s'ha d'establir en hexadecimal:"

msgid ""
"\n"
"nft add table ip mangle\n"
"nft add rule ip mangle PREROUTING tcp sport 22 counter ip dscp set 0x04\n"
"nft add rule ip mangle PREROUTING tcp dport 22 counter ip dscp set 0x04"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"nft add table ip mangle\n"
"nft add rule ip mangle PREROUTING tcp sport 22 counter ip dscp set 0x04\n"
"nft add rule ip mangle PREROUTING tcp dport 22 counter ip dscp set 0x04"

msgid "Dynamic Routing"
msgstr "Encaminament dinàmic"

msgid "<primary>routing</primary><secondary>dynamic</secondary><seealso><command>frr</command></seealso>"
msgstr "<primary>encaminament</primary><secondary>dinàmic</secondary><seealso><command>frr</command></seealso>"

msgid "<primary><command>frr</command></primary>"
msgstr "<primary><command>frr</command></primary>"

msgid "<primary><command>quagga</command></primary><see><command>frr</command></see>"
msgstr "<primary><command>quagga</command></primary><see><command>frr</command></see>"

msgid "<primary><command>zebra</command></primary><see><command>frr</command></see>"
msgstr "<primary><command>zebra</command></primary><see><command>frr</command></see>"

msgid "The reference tool for dynamic routing is currently <command>frr</command> from the similarly-named package; it used to be <command>quagga</command>, and before that <command>zebra</command> until development of these stopped. However, <command>frr</command> kept the names of the programs for compatibility reasons which explains the <command>zebra</command> commands below."
msgstr "L'eina de referència per a l'encaminament dinàmic és actualment <command>frr</command>, del paquet del mateix nom; havia estat <command>quagga</command>, i abans encara <command>zebra</command>, fins que es va aturar el desenvolupament d'aquests. No obstant això, <command>frr</command> va mantenir els noms dels programes per raons de compatibilitat que expliquen les ordres <command>zebra</command> més avall."

msgid "<emphasis>BACK TO BASICS</emphasis> Dynamic routing"
msgstr "<emphasis>TORNAR A LES BASES</emphasis> Encaminament dinàmic"

msgid "Dynamic routing allows routers to adjust, in real time, the paths used for transmitting IP packets. Each protocol involves its own method of defining routes (shortest path, use routes advertised by peers, and so on)."
msgstr "L'encaminament dinàmic permet als «routers» ajustar, en temps real, els camins utilitzats per transmetre paquets IP. Cada protocol implica el seu propi mètode de definició de rutes (el camí més curt, les rutes d'ús anunciades per d'altres, etc.)."

msgid "<primary><command>ip</command></primary><secondary><literal>route</literal></secondary>"
msgstr "<primary><command>ip</command></primary><secondary><literal>route</literal></secondary>"

msgid "<primary><command>route</command></primary>"
msgstr "<primary><command>route</command></primary>"

msgid "In the Linux kernel, a route links a network device to a set of machines that can be reached through this device. The <command>ip</command> command, when <literal>route</literal> is used as the first argument, defines new routes and displays existing ones. The <command>route</command> command was used for that purpose, but it is deprecated in favor of <command>ip</command>."
msgstr "En el nucli de Linux, una ruta enllaça un dispositiu de xarxa amb un conjunt de màquines a les quals es pot arribar a través d'aquest dispositiu. L'ordre <command>ip</command>, quan s'utilitza com a primer argument <literal>route</literal> , defineix noves rutes i mostra les existents. L'ordre <command>route</command> s'havia usat amb aquest propòsit, però ha quedat obsoleta a favor d'<command>ip</command>."

msgid "FRR (FRRouting) is a set of daemons cooperating to define the routing tables to be used by the Linux kernel; each routing protocol (most notably BGP, OSPF and RIP) provides its own daemon(s). The <literal>zebra</literal> and <literal>staticd</literal> daemons, which are always started, collect information from other daemons and handle static routing tables accordingly. The other daemons are known as <command>bgpd</command>, <command>ospfd</command>, <command>ospf6d</command>, <command>ripd</command>, <command>ripngd</command>, <command>isisd</command>, etc."
msgstr "FRR (FRRouting) és un conjunt de dimonis que cooperen per definir les taules d'encaminament que ha d'utilitzar el nucli de Linux; cada protocol d'encaminament (especialment BGP, OSPF i RIP) proporciona el seu propi dimoni(s). Els dimonis <literal>zebra</literal> i <literal>staticd</literal>, que sempre estan en funcionament, recopilen informació d'altres dimonis i gestionen les taules d'encaminament estàtiques en conseqüència. Els altres dimonis es coneixen com <command>bgpd</command>, <command>ospfd</command>, <command>ospf6d</command>, <command>ripd</command>, <command>ripng</command>, <command>isisd</command>, etc."

